  "prompt": "Can men feel the hymen when they insert their penis into the vagina?",
  "response": "The hymen is a thin membrane that partially covers the vaginal opening. It varies in shape, thickness, and flexibility among individuals. When a penis is inserted into the vagina, the sensation of the hymen can vary depending on several factors, including the individual's anatomy and the presence of lubrication.\n\nIn many cases, the hymen is flexible and may stretch or tear during first-time penetration, which might not be felt distinctly by either partner. Some people might experience a sensation of resistance or tightness, but this can be due to various factors, not just the hymen.\n\nIt's important to note that the presence or absence of a hymen does not indicate virginity or sexual activity, as the hymen can be stretched or torn by various non-sexual activities, such as sports or tampon use.\n\nOverall, while some men might feel a slight sensation, it's not a guarantee, and the experience can vary widely. Communication and comfort between partners are key to a positive sexual experience.",
